{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"86b62966-8767-4eb6-8938-8762114a0e6c","content":"Here are **3 performance anti-patterns** found in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. File I/O via Property Function (EvalHeavy.csproj:13)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n**Problem:** `ReadAllText` performs synchronous disk I/O during evaluation. Property functions that hit the filesystem block the evaluator and don't benefit from caching.\n**Fix:** Read the file at build time in a target instead of during evaluation, or use an item include if you just need the path.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Recursive Wildcard Glob (EvalHeavy.csproj:9)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n**Problem:** `**\\*.*` forces MSBuild to enumerate the *entire* directory tree during evaluation. In large repos this is very expensive and scales with file count. It also triggers re-evaluation whenever any file changes.\n**Fix:** Narrow the glob to specific extensions/directories (e.g., `**\\*.txt`) or move the item into a target so it runs only at build time.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deeply Chained Imports (3 levels)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\n**Problem:** Each `<Import>` adds an XML parse + evaluate pass. Deep chains multiply this cost and make the evaluation graph harder for MSBuild to cache.\n**Fix:** Flatten into a single `.props` file or at most one level of nesting to reduce parse overhead.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** The biggest offenders are the property-function file read and the recursive wildcard glob—both scale poorly and block evaluation. The nested imports add overhead but are less severe at only 3 levels. Addressing the first two will yield the most improvement.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4016ce39-075c-4f19-ac20-493e972c6275","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a complete picture of the project. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues:\n\n1. **Deeply nested import chain**: `level1.props` → `level2.props` → `level3.props` (3 levels deep). Each import requires MSBuild to parse and evaluate another XML file.\n\n2. **Overly broad wildcard glob**: `<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" ...>` - This recursive wildcard pattern forces MSBuild to walk the entire directory tree during evaluation. This is very expensive, especially in large repositories.\n\n3. **File I/O during evaluation via property function**: `$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))` - This reads a file's entire contents into a property during evaluation. \n\nThe property functions that perform disk I/O are particularly problematic since they block the entire evaluation process while waiting for file access to complete.","outputTokens":678,"requestId":"040C:3B8D06:68C0AD9:7196EFD:69F01077"},"id":"6ad6a84c-8a1a-4979-91d8-5b99a40cc399","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:42:30.266Z","parentId":"0b465494-770b-4be1-8c5c-9b503dd4bf01"}
